choices.text:
going to be by a bus (I did say it was Honduras), and you most often will get off the bus 1km and so back from your final destination. You will be among the first to arrive and the last to leave. Your time might be worth an hour and a half or two hours, not including the potentially long waits in line to drink pure cane sugar sugar from the river. Your hard earned Cuesta Cola hidden treasures will be spent taking out a bus to potentially a village 10km away you will have to take back to the store from which to then walk back at least 5km of dirt road.

It really puts grocery shopping in perspective. Bless you supermarket workers keeping the grocery aisles going smoothly and clean. God bless your backs.

Wash day, chop day, and market day. Monkey brain, feel the molecules in your body, they are breathing you in, breathing you out, speaking to you like a child, and telling you what it is that you are. Instead you listen to the monkey brain run wild.

Some things are too important to wash behind the refrigerator, there will be another day. Some potatoes are too important to clean. Some globs of veggies and meat are too important to include. Strawberries are too important to wash. They will be air dry within 10 minutes, or so.

Expensive cigars are like Satan driving a stake through one's head, killing live and leaving a hole a one and a half inches wide.
